      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Richardson extrapolation or equivalent grid convergence index study demonstrating discretization error below 5% for hemolysis QoI across all operating points.",
      "rationale": "Grid convergence study was performed at three refinement levels and GCI computed. Discretization error is below 10% at most operating points but exceeds 5% at two high-shear conditions near the impeller tip. Achieved level 3 does not meet required level 4."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental test conditions must match COU operating envelope (flow rate, rotational speed, fluid properties) within stated tolerances; full uncertainty characterization of test measurements required.",
      "rationale": "Experimental data from FDA generic pump bench tests cover only 3 of 5 required flow-speed combinations. Fluid viscosity in bench tests used bovine blood rather than human blood analog, introducing systematic condition mismatch. Achieved level 2 below required level 4."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metric (e.g., validation metric M) computed with experimental uncertainty bounds; prediction intervals must overlap experimental intervals at all assessed operating points.",
      "rationale": "Qualitative agreement between CFD and experimental hemolysis index is observed at 3 operating points. However, no formal validation metric has been computed and prediction intervals are not reported. Quantitative discrepancy exceeds experimental uncertainty at one operating point. Achieved level 2 below required level 4."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "The primary QoI (normalized index of hemolysis, NIH) directly maps to the clinical acceptance threshold; secondary QoIs (shear stress distribution, exposure time) are validated independently.",
      "rationale": "NIH is used as the primary QoI and maps directly to the clinical threshold. Shear stress distributions are reported but not independently validated against experimental PIV data. Secondary QoI coverage is partial. Achieved level 3 below required level 4."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation activities must be conducted on the same device geometry and under COU-representative operating conditions; any surrogate geometry must be justified with similarity analysis.",
      "rationale": "Validation was performed on the FDA generic pump geometry, which is a surrogate for the actual VAD device. No formal geometric similarity analysis has been documented. Operating conditions in validation activities cover only a subset of the COU envelope. Achieved level 2 below required level 4."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
