      "acceptanceCriteria": "Iterative convergence criteria and round-off error bounds documented; residuals reduced by at least 6 orders of magnitude for all transported quantities.",
      "rationale": "Solver convergence monitoring was not systematically documented across all 5 operating points. Residual reduction criteria were specified in the simulation plan but convergence logs were not archived for independent review. Factor flagged as epistemic gap at MRL 5; achieved level 1."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Independent review of simulation setup inputs, boundary conditions, and post-processing scripts by a qualified analyst not involved in original simulation.",
      "rationale": "No independent review of simulation inputs or post-processing procedures has been conducted. Use error assessment is identified as an epistemic gap; the simulation team performed internal checks only. Achieved level 1 below required level 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Justification for selection of turbulence model and hemolysis damage model with sensitivity analysis demonstrating model form uncertainty is bounded and acceptable for the COU.",
      "rationale": "The power-law hemolysis damage model (Giersiepen-Wurzinger) is used without formal justification of model form selection or sensitivity analysis comparing alternative damage models. Model form uncertainty is unquantified. Epistemic gap flagged at MRL 5; achieved level 1."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "All model input parameters characterized with probability distributions; Monte Carlo propagation of input uncertainty through hemolysis QoI with convergence of output statistics demonstrated.",
      "rationale": "Monte Carlo UQ was initiated but input parameter distributions for blood viscosity and damage model exponents were assigned based on literature ranges without patient-specific characterization. Output statistics show marginal convergence at 500 samples. Achieved level 2 below required level 4; gap flagged."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Sufficient replicate experimental measurements to characterize aleatory variability in hemolysis measurements; statistical power analysis supporting sample size adequacy.",
      "rationale": "Experimental hemolysis measurements consist of single-run data at each operating point with no replication. Variability in NIH measurement due to blood sample preparation and assay protocol is uncharacterized. No statistical power analysis performed. Epistemic gap; achieved level 1."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
